  <Placemark>
   <name>Small Craft Advisory issued October 11 at 2:33PM EDT until October 11 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Mount Holly NJ</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_minor</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, east winds 15 to 20 kt
with gusts up to 25 kt and seas 4 to 5 ft. For the Storm
Warning, northeast winds 30 to 40 kt with gusts up to 50 kt
and seas 12 to 17 ft expected.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Sandy Hook to Manasquan Inlet NJ
out 20 nm.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 6 PM EDT this
evening. For the Storm Warning, from 6 PM this evening to 8 PM
EDT Monday.

* IMPACTS...Storm force winds and hazardous seas will capsize or
damage vessels and reduce visibility.</Snippet>
