  <Placemark>
   <name>Flood Advisory issued October 11 at 11:58AM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_minor</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>...The National Weather Service in Grand Junction has issued a Flood
Advisory for the following rivers in Colorado...

San Juan River at Pagosa Springs affecting Archuleta County.

For the San Juan River...including Pagosa Springs...elevated river
levels are forecast.

* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...San Juan River at Pagosa Springs.

* WHEN...From this morning until further notice.

* IMPACTS...At 10.3 feet, Water is flowing over the yards of homes
in the San Juan River Village northeast of Pagosa Springs.
At 11.0 feet, Water will approach the area around the River Center
shopping complex in Pagosa Springs. Inundation of  sections of
Hermosa Street and low land areas adjacent to the river can be
expected.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 11:00 AM MDT Saturday the stage was 9.0 feet.
- Bankfull stage is 8.5 feet.
- Forecast...The river is expected to potentially reach minor
flood stage due to recent rainfall.
- Action stage is 9.5 feet.
- Flood stage is 10.5 feet.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood</Snippet>
