  <Placemark>
   <name>Flash Flood Warning issued October 11 at 10:14AM MST until October 11 at 4:15PM MST by NWS Flagstaff AZ</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_severe</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>FFWFGZ

The National Weather Service in Flagstaff has issued a

* Flash Flood Warning for...
Coconino County in north central Arizona...

* Until 415 PM MST /515 PM MDT/ Saturday.

* At 1014 AM MST /1114 AM MDT/, stream gauges on the Moenkopi Wash,
located just south of Moenkopi, indicate that Flash Flooding is
ongoing. Rises of about 6 feet have already noted and further
rises are possible, due to widespread rainfall along the drainage.

HAZARD...Life threatening flash flooding. Heavy rain producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Automated stream gauges.

IMPACT...Life threatening flash flooding of creeks and streams.

This includes the following creeks, washes and rivers...
Moenkopi Wash, Hamblin Wash and Begashibito Wash.</Snippet>
